   Actually can we make still another change ? (Not sure if I should just repush to this branch)
   
   In HdfsOptions::FromUri display the warning only if the scheme is viewfs
   ```
    std::string host;
     if (useHdfs3) {
       if (uri.scheme() == "viewfs") {
         ARROW_LOG(WARNING)
             << "viewfs://namenode resolves to hdfs://namenode with hdfs3 driver.";
       }
       host = uri.host();
     } else {
       host = uri.scheme() + "://" + uri.host();
     }
   ```
   
   Like this the warning won't display on clusters where viewfs is not activated (like in the pyarrow integrations tests)

